{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9336d9c0-2483-4c78-97db-1fa28e64ab7d","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle event mappings** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup) via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the activity is paused\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the activity is stopped\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs when the app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`ConfigureLifecycleEvents`** is called on the `MauiAppBuilder`.\n- Use **`#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS`** preprocessor directives to keep platform code compiling only on the target.\n- The `AddAndroid` / `AddiOS` extension methods expose the full set of native lifecycle callbacks (`OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `WillTerminate`, etc.).\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` to get the extension methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a1aa8749-966d-4647-b612-1efbbe02bc8c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":402,"requestId":"B7CC:21FC92:1306B9:1922C2:69FFD82B"},"id":"ad6432e0-9fec-4974-94c2-40b5f8efac7c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:58:26.897Z","parentId":"89e66db2-84d1-4b36-8958-77f489b3abec"}
